Kheldar will give Mordanith the following information (in a Div. warded
location) regarding the Farm Teams and the Magic items:
  In addition to any items that were removed from the Wizard Kings citadel,
any enchanted items that are ""acquired"" by the members of the Monastery or
the Church of Odin are sent to the Isle of Law to be analyzed and
cataloged.  As long as the person's superior has no objections and no
dangerous enchantments are found to be hidden within the item, if the
person that ""acquired"" the item would like to have it, it is returned to
him with any information that was gained about it (if that is appropriate).
 All other items are retained for further storage and analysis.

Although you have access to the ""management"" of each monastery, in order to
discuss magic items for the Farm Teams you will need to either go to the
Isle of Law or the main monastery in Marden.  I suggest the main monastery
in Marden.  Although the process will take longer in the monastery (because
the items are stored at the Isle of Law), the head research guy at the
Monastery has direct experience with many of the items that were recovered
from the Wizard King.  Also, from a Balance perspective, it probably is
better if you don't make a personal appearance at the central location for
the Church of Odin.

By the way, if any of your Farm Teams find items that they want researched,
sold, stored or otherwise disposed of, please feel free to ""direct"" them to
one of the Monasteries.  Although they won't be told that this is the case,
you will be treated as their ""superior"" with regards to decisions about the
items.

