I do have the layout and even a graphic file that I can send you if you
want it and can tell me your format of choice.  It may actually be more
useful to Myth than anyone else (without a little massaging, that is) since
I created it with MacDraw and I assume that you are still using a Mac.  I
will get the file when I go home tonight and try to get it sent out in
e-mail Saturday.  Here are the basics (assuming minimal variation as a
result of intermediate reality shifts) [I think that ranks in Legal-ese is
going to be a requirement for entities who are aware of and discuss
existing in a multiple reality framework!].  

Marden is the intersection of 12 line segments (twelve pieces of string
tied in the center).  The previous ""normal"" structure resulted in a high
concentration of power at the intersection of those lines.  I believe that
that was the center of the city.  After the repair of the damaged lines, a
view from above using a W:Abjuration filter would show an evenly
distributed web of nodes.  Each node has, I believe - and the graphic will
give the actual info - three line segments tied together.  

This distribution has the effect of making the entire structure more
resilient.  The destruction or Fraying of several nodes would not destroy
the overall integrity of the structure.  Also, this brought more power to
the edges of the structure (and thereby the city).  Although there was no
longer an extreme concentration at the location of the previous node, a
chart of the ambient mana distribution would still show the concentration
highest at the center of the web.  The difference now is that the
distribution of Mana is mathematically even.  Picture the distribution of
stars in the milky way galaxy.

Since we didn't actually have a map of the City that we could overlay the
grid on, Alex has been somewhat flexible in the discussions of where these
""mini-nodes"" are actually located.  I am assuming that the Council will
take by eminent domain (if they don't already have it) the real estate
located at the outermost set of mini-nodes in the web.  These would be the
key areas to build anchors for the City's magical defense system.

Chris


