"Bardic Tales","Hello everyone.  On February 9, 1998, our beloved GM (OK, maybe that's a
bit much for some of you), sent out an e-mail message about having someone
in each group manage minor record keeping and dates.  He also asked for
someone to coordinate that information.  When no one else responded, I
volunteered to do the create the ""Timeline of Events"".

Although I knew that several runs had occurred between then and now, I
waited to see if I would get any information, either from Alex or anyone
else.  It has now been 3 months and I have not received anything (except
for the initial two e-mail responses from Jim Smith and Dave Wall).  

I realize that gaming in Bardic Tales probably is more important to me than
it is to anyone else (I can practically hear some of you saying ""get a
life"" :-)  ), but keeping even minor records is a benefit to everyone, not
just fanatics like me.

The first benefit is that Alex is running multiple groups and record
keeping helps him remember who did what when.

The second benefit is that none of us (including me) feel that gaming is
more important than working or family.   (OK, I would take the day off to
game, but I am the exception to the rule)  Therefore, we rarely think about
our characters so much that we walk into a run with a full understanding of
exactly what we were doing the last time we got together to run our character.

The third benefit is that we create a group ""story"" which adds depth beyond
what would exist  if Alex was just running our group and no other.

A perfect example of this is what is happening between the MKP group and
the Shapeshifters group.  There is a lot of cross group interaction
occurring.  It just so happens that my (Shapeshifters) character's
Significant Other is having a relationship with someone in MKP.  My
character doesn't know anything about this.  What is the time differential
between the two groups -- Alex may know now, but who will be able to say in
a few months (real time) when my character may find out during a run what
is going on?

Wouldn't it be of benefit to Morag or Maeve to find out what/when Mordanith
makes a deal with Madra to modify Nature in some way?  Wouldn't it be of
benefit to Morphus to find out when Miriel is playing with Kalarina and
Sigmund in Bachus' love spa?  Wouldn't Adrienne like to know when Kay has
led a Tolnian legion against the forces of Death in Bengali?  And wouldn't
Vardigan like to know when the balance of power in the town he is about to
attack has shifted because of.....

To bring this message to a close: anyone getting this message has e-mail.
All I ask is this: ask Alex what the date is when you run and type up a
brief (whatever YOU want) summary of your run.  Send this information to me
in an e-mail message and I will collate the data, send it to Alex, and he
will disperse it as appropriate.  I'll even collate the information that is
sent to me from all members of a group and send it back to them before
their next run date if I get it from multiple people in a group. 

Thanks for taking the time to read this message,
Chris
