"THE BALANCE. part 4 of 4","
They moved through the Void.  They watched, though any meaningful comparison
between what they did and human sense impressions would be ridiculous.  For
our story we will say they watched and we will speak of their bodies.

They looked out and watched some more.  They ""saw"" the Bright One and the
Mother embraced and twined against each other, deeply penetrating each other
in a lover's grip.  She Who Waits covered them like a blanket as if to hide
their indiscretions from the Void.

The Bright One moved inside the Mother and she sighed and shifted against
him.  He gripped her closer and they moved together.  The Watchers eye kept
going to the bed in which the Mother and the Bright One embraced- for they
had made it.  Woven of different thoughts, contrasting, scintillating and
beautiful they watched as it danced and shimmered against the skin of the
two lovers.  They watched as the light and dark, threads unwinding and
reforming, chased themselves across the bed and admired their handiwork.  A
thing of beauty.  They both nodded, satisfied.  It would last until the
lovers were done.  No element too strong, no unbinding too fast- a true work
of artistry.  An objet d'art in perfect balance.

They watched for something like a time, and then, satisfied, they left
again.

