"RE: Images","Hmmm..

Fire Mountain:

A gigantic volcano surrounded by black glowing clouds at it's summit. It is
sitting in a gigantic impact crater.  That is shaped like a pie dish....
mostly flat and then steep cliffs on all sides.  Fire Mountain itself is a
broad, squat shape- VERY VERY high, but extraordinarily broad- sitting in
the middle of it.  Cities are scattered up and down the slope of the
mountain...

Occasionally dark shadowed dragons can be seen flying around the volcano....
Also: its dark.  Unfiltered sunlight never hits the crater.  At BEST- very
rare- it could be a foggy daylight!

The Bridge:

Surrounds the world, but it is so big that when you are on it it looks like
a flat plane with knee high mist(just under eye-level for sigmund).  There
are ""stripes"" or ""lanes"" or light pouring underneath the mist to cause the
colors of the rainbow.  The ""sky"" is rolling dark blue clouds- like storm
clouds against a dark blue background.  If you stare at them too long you
see the shapes of things to come, or might come, or those things that have
come, or might have come....  Occasionally shapes made of blue mist will
bubble out of the mist and then disappear into it again.
