"Tactical Situation","
You know, it just occured to me that we are going into a highly dangerous tactical situation this Sunday and it might be very beneficial to have a plan.
 
Here is the situation as I remember it.  We are located in a wide gully.  The gully is more than a mile wide but the main corridor (flat section) is only about 900 yds wide, to the side of which are rising slopes.  The sides of the gully are probably cliffs but I suspect that tactically they will be out of the picture.
 
We are situated at a spot in the gully where two berms (small rises in the terrain) cross the gully floor.  The berms are aproximately 300 yds apart and are tall enough to block LOS of normal humans (and probably even the big guy).
 
There is a large army aproaching the area from (lets call it for the sake of argument) the west.  This army consists of a large number of undead, mostly ghouls with a few ghasts (or was it mostly zombies with a few ghouls).  There are also a small number of Necromancers and a large proto-dragon in the lead.  The proto-dragon seems to have the reality mass profile of a small dragon but appears much more physical rather than magical.  We have no information about it's intelligence.  The head of the army is 1 mile away.  1/4 mile away is a line of lethar scouts preceding the main troops.  The following troop composition was obtained by Kor'Keth on a scouting mission.
 
For assets on our side we have: Sigmund, Kor'Keth, D'Jan, Mordenaith, Morphus, E-Man, Khalid, Arack, Mr. Justicar(whats his name?), Kilsorana (the talking horse), Muriel and the Storm Warden.  As I recall neither Pentos or Peter came and the SandWalker went home alone.  We do not have a holocaust cloak or a wheel barrel.
 
Oh, yeah.  I forget to mention we are in a level 7 mana storm.  If he concentrates real hard the area around Morphus (expanding radius, call it 30') can become ordered down to a level of say, mana storm 3 unsing the staff of law.  I can do the same thing in a much smaller radius using enforce reality. Khalid can raise a shield which blocks it out real good but then we cant do anything.
 
First Question:  
 
Is the above summary accurate?
 
Second Question:  
 
How many lethar are in the scouting line and is it a line or do they move back to physically communicate with the main force periodically?
 
Also how big is the main force OOM?  Thousands of undead?  Tens of thousands? Hundreds?  Also how many necromancers could we see?  Any other mages?  Any obvious generals?
 
THE PLAN
 
I think we should set up two groups of mages on opposite sides of the gorge to shoot into the masses when they come between us...
 
No really,  I think we should pick an advance team.  This team (probably Myself, D'Jan, Kor'Keth and Muriel) will dig in on the lee side of the first berm.  The idea is that they will hide and the Lethar will walk right over them whee upon they can appear out of the dust and kill them before they can report back.
 
I though of sticking Arak in the advanced team but his smell of life might be too easily tracked by a Lethar.  I am assuming that Muriel has some secret technique which she can use to remain hidden. Is she a combat babe?  If not there is no reason to force her up front.  Also I am assuming there are not hundreds of Lethar in which case we would be dead.  Tens would even probably kill us.
 
In support of this does anyone ranged attacks which are silent and likely to work in a mana storm (Arak could use missile weapons here if they had enough range).
 
The remainder of my plan was to split the mages into two groups and set them up at the corners of the second berm building a killing field in the valley between.  After our advanced group took out the Lethar we would retreat (probably taking the bodies with us) and allow the main force to come into the valley.  Once the significant players where in the advance force could block forward progress at the second berm and the two mage groups could lay waste to every one with debilitating cross fire.  We should just avoid anything as destructive as a bolt of damnation again (though it worked great before).
 
It would be nice to mine the killing field ahead of time but we would have to e careful that the Lethar or the advance team did not set them off by accident or the main host would be warned.  We also might want to consider whether we have a mop up plan if we do manage to kill off the big baddies.  Clean up on a huge horde could be tough and it would be really nice if there were no survivors.
 
Unfortunately my belief, based on past experience, is that the minute someone significant dies The Liche will know his past (unless Morphus can pull some cool Orb Ops to suck them souls).  Thus, though I don't think they will be fast we could face reinforcements.  We should have an escape plan.
 
I suggest the following for the two fire groups:
 
Morphus, Kilsorana, E-Man, Storm Warden
Arak, Mordenaith, Khalid, Mr. Justicar
 
Anything else?  What attack modes do people plan to use?  I am going to be almost exclusively physical this battle.
 

 
 
