        [Jim JM]
        I would welcome any suggestion that did not involve me as
the defensive nexus of the party.


        [Myth]
        I agree.  Mordanith is much better as an offensive nexus.


        [Pook]
        Are these beam weapons or radius blasts?  Do you need to
be a mage to use one?

        [Jim JM]
        Beam weapons. Greater spread than a shotgun but not much
greater (normally).
        Just aim, pull down the trigger guard collar and press the
button. Shielding the eyes
        is sometimes a good idea.


        [Myth]
        While these are great against Lethar,  I'm not sure they
are subtle enough for that.  If I were running an army (even a
zombie army), I'd be suspicious if my scouts went over a ridge,
there was a big flask of light, and nobody reported back.

         Also, I believe that I can make a decent set of mines
based on light and life that would be pretty nasty (just hard to
        hide )

        [Pook]
        If you do this I think you would need to use some of your
order potions to prevent them from going off prematurely.  At army
advancement speeds we should have some time between Lethar impact
and Horde impact.  If we assume they are moving at 2'/ct [ALEX? -
There are zombies in the horde] and there is a 3/4 mi gap (~3900
ft) that gives us about 6.5 minutes to deal with the lethar and
set up before the horde crests the hill.  Boy, that is shorter
than I expected.


        [Myth]
        6.5 minutes?  After what we did in the castle in 2.5
seconds?  We'll have time for a fight, a breakfast buffet, some
landscaping and a nice in-your-face ritual to meet Pete's Dragon
(TM by Disney) and his zombie hordes!

        Okay, I exaggerate.  But that is a long time in BT combat.
I might even be able to get in a spell or two.


        A Big Question for me is :

        Why is this force sortying ? A land force of this
composition strikes me as being more useful against
        some sort of massed troops (Brigade and such) that we
haven't really seen. Otherwise I would expect that the
        high-power baddies would simply head where they needed to
be at a fast clip. Do they need these troops as
        screening forces ? to overwhelm a highpower good guy whose
primary skill is in melee ?

        I would love to have some idea of what their mission is .
It would help use counter them. We might be able to screw
        the up simply by delaying them. Slagging them is all to
the good but it may not be the best move.

        [Pook]

        Excellant questions.


        [Myth]
        I agree.  Excellent questions.  But we may not have the
time (despite previous comments) to do good research here,
especially through divinatory means.  If the local future here
isn't some sort of temporal soup, I'll eat my turban.

        While I'm commenting, I think the Ward Nine (I know,
Britt, not the real number.  But it sounds cool.) might be a good
place to do some of the more delicate setup stuff.  Storm Warden
has stated that he can't do that Elemental thing for the whole
party in this mana storm, and I'm not sure I could set up the ABS
(Abjurational Blasting Shield) easily in one, though it could
probably maintain after fairly well.

        I would suggest the following distribution:


        Phase One: Lethar Away

        Somehow ambush scouts, and destroy them well and subtly
enough so the army doesn't catch on.

        Mordanith, Khalid - blasters
        Kilsorana - hampering the opposition by further
destabilizing their environment
        Morphus - hoovering up lost souls with his Orb.
        Various Fortu - physical combatants
        Storm Warden - making sure they don't escape
        Erithmaeon - damping the output so the army doesn't see
        Rujah - watcher
        Muriel?


        Phase Two: Get 'Em

        Wait for unsuspecting army (back up one ridge to prepared
position?) and Let 'Em Have It.

        Khalid (with Web trigger), two Fortu (with Sunbane
triggers), Mordanith, Morphus - blasters
        Erithmaeon, Kilsorana, Storm Lord - defense, second salvo

        After that it gets hard to predict.  I'd assign Khalid to
general mayhem (sandblasting the army, perhaps), Morphus,
Mordanith, and Kilsorana to more specific mayhem (vargoyles and
necromancers), Rujah as spotter, Erithmaeon and Storm Warden to
defense, and Muriel and the Fortu to whatever seems to fit their
needs and abilities.

        The more I think about it, the more I like Eman having the
ABS up and holding down the Utility Mage spot.

                                                   -Myth, now in
COLOR!

        Another thought-- an air shield connecting the two berms,
with dirt on top.  Let the scouts walk over us, then attack from
below, or drop 'em, or drop 'em and resolidify the shield leaving
'em stuck, or something else creative, petty, and cruel.
