"Nureyev","Just thought I woud ramble randomly about Nureyev for a few moments to let the gray cells unwind a little.

Physical Description
Nureyev is about 6'4"" tall and weighs a good bit over 200 pounds.  What would be typical for a highly muscular person of that hieght?  300#?  He has the build of a professional weightlifter.  Nureyev's skin is a deep black.  Closer to the deep black of Seal (a musician whom I like a lot) rather than the coffee black of alot of the coloured people we see in the entertainment industry.  He also does not have a single hair on his body.  OK I lied, he has eyebrows and nose hairs and things like that but he is bald as an egg.  Actually Nureyev's appearance is not at all unusual for a denizen of the jungles of Venn (I picture him as the classic Nubian).  He is a bit more muscular and massive than most of that region (which tend towards strong and wiry rather than strong and massive) but otherwise would blend in fairly well.  Well, except for the modifications.  

When Nureyev walked out of the Venn jungle into Tharuden this is what he looked like but there has been one minor alteration since then.  Embedded in a pattern resembling a tonsur around the side and back of his head are a number of glowing orange-red crystals.  These crystals average about 1"" to 2"" in length and when unlit have an burnt orangish color and a texture somewhere between quartz and resin.  On a constant basis (even while he is asleep) red and orange sparks can be seen travelling through the crystals and an occasional glow blooms, expands and then faeds away.  It appears as if the crystals are actually attached to his head and some people theorize that they penetrate into his brain.  Nureyev installed these crystals in himself a few hundred years after the Fortu were developed.  Some people say that in addition to looking unusual there have been several personality changes since the crystals were installed.  Then again it is hard to tell since he was not the most traditional person in the first place.

Personality
Nureyev is often seen walking around almost completely naked (small loin cloth and a utility belt) and definately prefers the minimum amount of clothing required.  On the other hand he enjoys jewelry and may often be seen wearing necklaces, arm and ankle braces and head chains in the Tharuden style.  He is also prone to carry gadgets and objects around with him and when he does were more clothing it is usualy in order to have more pockets.  Nureyev has a detached and philosophical manner.  He is renowned for being able to view any situation form an impartial perspective and find the humor in it.  His laugh, and hearty deep belly laugh, was a trademark of his and was renowned around Koreth and the  courts of the world (at least the ones were he was welcome).  Sometimes his air of detachment caused concern and even resentment.  Nureyev was the kind of person who could take intense interest in a small garden or the plight of an individual begger and then shrug off the massacre of a Tolnian century as if it were nothing.  Many times the humor which he found in a situation was not appreciated by those who felt they had a stronger interest in the outcome.

At about the time that he installed the crystals in his head his behavior also seemed a bit more abberant.  Always a bit unusual from the odd perspective render by his study of the Eldar Drawing and Alteration arts he was already known to be prone to seemingly non-sensical statements.  Nueyev was often frequented for advice on various matters arcance but it was considered part of the price of the knowledge that you had to spend a lot of effort tracing the bizarre connections that he made before you felt you understood the answer.  Even from this basis of oddity though the change after the crystals was noticiable.  Nureyev began treating everything in a mechanical and objective manner; People, relationships, emotions.  His previous highly social and amiable style became very efficient and terse.  This was most dramatically seen right after the crystals were installed (probably an adjustment period) and his personality soon returned to a more amiable level (after a few hundered years or so) however he was still always subject to bouts of mechanical behavior and there was the sense that something was always held back in his interactions.

There are rumours that just prior to this period was a point of personal depression in Nureyev's life and that one aspect of the descent into his work was as a means of escape from some tragedy he was unwilling to face.

