"Gaming Thought","You know it occured to me recently that spiders are bugs.

This upcoming mission will represent only the third time that Sigmund has seen a bug in his 10-odd years of gaming.

1.    The StarTrek bugs which fell in though our hole in reality.  My weren't they a pain in the ass.

2.    A bunch of sickly bugs which I ran across while wandering around on Kalarina's lands (it might have been Dora's lands).  I think this may have been an MKP run I was sitting in on.  They were big but they were also near death from some strange decay based fungus and so they really didn't give us much hassle.

3.    Magic resistant large underwater spiders.

Hmmmm, perhaps this may be even more challenging than I had anticipated.

As a possible semi-bug I have always thought that Trolls hand an insect derivation becuase of their six limbd status but that is probably not true since they are very recent on the global scale of things.

BTW:  As a side note, if there are no bugs in Alex's world then where does silk come from?  After all, we have actually interacted with the silk mission.  It must come from somewhere.  Are worms not bugs?  In this world is there a silk plant?  Or are they just the rare exception to the no bug rule?  What about honey?  Has a player character ever eaten honey?  I am willing to bet that plant pollination is dependant on some aspect of elemental nature rather than bugs just like decomposing bodies is elemental decay.



