"Shapeshifters","Just as a strawman here is a proposal for a first attempt ritual for
returning home (courtesy of Ritual Designs 'R Us a wholly owned subsidiary
of Big Ass Power Pushers).

Intention:

The intention of this ritual is to form the first part in a two part plan
for escape.  The first part (this ritual) is to create (affirm) the reality
that the Slaad gate is actually a reality bubble trap that has formed a
pocket reality around us but is still fundamentally attached to the epoch 5
prime (location of capture).  The second part of the plan is to then escape
from the reality pocket back to a slightly safer location on the prime than
the one we left.

Overview:

The ritual is composed of the following steps: preparation, isolation,
purification, consensus, surrender and revelation.  Each of these steps is
as follows:

Preparation - each person should do whatever is necessary to prepare
themselves for their role in the ritual.

Isolation - we build a big fucking reality ward around ourselves isolating
us from all other interactions from the pocket reality (before we have even
started we have to agree that we are not really in the third epoch at all).

Purification - Each person should acknowledge and shed all attachment that
they have to being in the third epoch.  Each person should also enter the
best state of meditation.

Consensus - The group should establish a unified consensus about what
exactly the fifth epoch is and about there commitment to get out of the
illusory pocket reality in which we are now trapped.

Surrender - Each person must voluntarily give up any thoughts that this is
anything other than a reality pocket and any memories which conflict with
that.  This would be a discipline II (at least since it is retoractive) cast
on yourself.  As far as discipline castings go it should be easier on the
scale of discipline IIs since it really is hard to tell the difference
between an illusory pocket reality and the thing it is emulating.  It will
be hard because we are targetting complete low level belief of the principle
without reservation.

Revelation - We drop the isolation ward and begin searching the pocket
reality for a way out.

A few notes about the implementation of these steps:

1.    Assuming it is still working I suspect Khalid would be the best at
maintaining an isolation sphere since for him it is the most fundamental
operation.

2.    Once we are isolated I would like to set up a mini-linking ward
situation as part of the ritual.  Integrating consensi (consensus?
consensa?) appears to be one of the primary functions of a ward and it would
probably help us immensly if we could objectively view the state of our
consensus.  On the flip side I don't think I can just pop into Ward mode.  I
was thinking more of linking up the other two Fortu in a local net, dropping
into strategy mode and holding the consensus visible in the way that I would
in ward mode but at a much simpler level.  This will also be helped by the
fact that we are only integrating a handful of people in this micro-reality.
I would expect to drop the ward functions before dropping the isolation
shield.

3.    If I do adopt a ward-like mode I suspect I will be a more passive
entity and the people who might best be able to leverage my capabilities
would probably be Kheldar (becuase of his experience and ward skills) and
E-man (because of his patterning).

4.    Khilsorana and Mordenaith (I suspect) have a good deal of enchantment
that may be useful as a basis here but I think this is fundamentally a
discipline casting rather than an enchantment.

5.    I suspect if we are to succesful we could actually rewind our
experience to the point of our entry and lose all memory of the ritual
(since why would you need a ritual if you are already in the pocket
reality).  To handle this circumstance I suggest we create a message
explaining that we just tried an escape ritual from the pocket reality and
if it doesn't work it is possible we won't remember it.  This will explain
why we are in an isolation shield.  I would suggest we place this message in
one of the Fortu brains (D'Jan or Peter - not myself) and lock it so that it
survives the ritual.    We can probably set it up autonomously enough so
that it deletes the trace memories of the context in which it was generated
after a certain interval.  That way there will be no trace.  I suggest D'jan
or Peter becuase (a) they are programmable and (b) they probably have the
smallest reality masses of any of us even considering they are Fortu.  I
think it would be a bad thing for Odin or myself (or really any of us) to
lock this memory even though we have the tools becuase its mere existence
would express a reservation on our parts in the rituals outcome.

Theoretically when the ritual is over we will probably not see anything
different from when it started so it really will be a question of whether we
the players are willing to believe we are in a pocket reality or really in
epoch 3.  After all, what really makes us think we aren't in a pocket
reality.  It is a much more reasonable idea.

I have an interesting feeling that the next couple of runs could end up
having the same feel as Total Recall where you can't distinguish between
illusion and reality.

Anyway, its a plan.  I can go to stage two design if we feel like the
fundamental principles are good.


