"Rebuilding Sigmund","Well since I am wounded I wanted figure out a few things.  The first is what
it means for a Fortu to have lost have his brain (and what Fortu wounds are
like) and the second is how I am going to be healed.  I wanted to see if
anybody had any interesting ideas for the latter (although I have to admit I
am going to be a little hesitant to try some things since it is my brain).

Of course this whole discussion presupposes that the party survives and
eventually finds my toasty body and also figures out how to get me out of
hard mode (which should all be pretty easy since Kheldar and 2 fortu are
with you).  It also assumes that I can stabilize (instead of disintegrating)
once I am no longer hard which may a more critical thing than the long term
healing.

Just for amusement I was wondering what a wound in a marble person might
look like so I wrote up the following description and ran it by Alex:

Observable damage [

Sigmund has a 1"" by 2"" whole in his left eye which appears to go into his
head.  Upon close examination it can be seen that the damage on the inside
appears to consist of an 18"" deep hole tapering to a point at the end.  The
surface of this hole is cracked and powdery stone (looking on the inside
more like a crushed porrous lattice  than solid marble - very much like
coral).  Crystalline powder can be seen to seep out of many of the holes in
the the inner surface of the wound.  A clear resinous goo also seeps from a
few channels as well as a grey mist with little sparks of lightning in it.
The wound is very cold.  If you were to touch the inside of the wound it
would be sharp (like steel wool or coral) except where it got melted by the
power blast.  Hopefully pretty soon after coming back around the resinous
goo will coat the inside of the wound preventing the gas from escaping any
more.  A slight crack runs from the eye down the left cheek ending at the
top lip (it probably runs an inch into the head along the upper palate).
While the sword is still in the wound cold sparks can be seen to run up and
down it.  There are no other signs of damage.

]

My first thought as to a plan once I am aware again is as follows:

Do some paramedic style stabilizing (time slow?  abjurational reinforcement?
lots of spackle?) -or-
Leave me in hard mode until you can get me to a Fortu lab.

There are three Fortu Lab that I know of:
  1.. The one at the ward that has the evil Rhysmaeon character at it whom I
don't want to be anywhere near.
  2.. A second one that I can't emtion but if someone suggested it would be
fine with me.
  3.. The partially completed one at the adventurers club (my ideal solution
and clearly the closest).
I think I need to be taken to one of these and stabilized more.

The next thing I think I need is a major operation.  I think this would
consist of the following things:
  1.. More in depth stabilization
  2.. A full systems check for other damage
  3.. Somebody growing a new batch of brain crystals
  4.. Slamming the new crystals in my head (or maybe growing them there in
the first place)
  5.. Doing some sort of restorative field so that all of the physical
elements combine together
This would be the extent of first stage healing.

I do not think that the physical eye which was destroyed is necessary for me
to see.  I think my senses are located in other ways.  Alex has not yet
confirmed this.  If the eye is not necessary to see I would rather leave the
wound open during second stage healing so that I have easy access to my
brain.  I may want to plug stuff into it or modify minor things so an easy
access portal would be handy.  We could always close the eye back up before
I do adventuring again.

I think first stage healing should be short (a few days) and would leave me
in a stable condition with greatly reduced physical and power damage (the
remainder of which can heal up at normal speeds over the next few months).
This is the time for second stage healing.

I believe that having half your brain destroyed is probably less of an issue
for Sigmund than for most (becuase of a number of things/not just being a
fortu).  What I think is likely to have happened is that much of Sigmunds
memory, language and certain types of skills are lost or degraded becuase of
the sudden loss of brain.  Becuase he is Sigmund though, I do not think this
loss needs to be a permanent thing.

Phase II healing for me I think will consist of rebuilding a set of memories
and skills that are consistent with who I say that I am.  I am viewing my
memories as just a first level cache for my true soul.  My soul defines my
identity and my memories and skills embody a form in the world that is
consistent with that identity.  I could lose the whole body and still have
an identity (framework) to rebuild it on.  I think of this as sort of a
higher level pattern.  Anyway, I think sigmund can take on something like
this because (a) he is a master dreamwalker/(Fortu Shape) Shifter and (b)
becuase he has access to the linking ward which has been watching him
intimately for a long time and is fairly well set up for doing this sort of
thing.  I think language skills will be the easiest things to restore (hell
at least one of my languages was just downloaded in the first place).  I
think the hardest things to restore will be any specific memories of things
that I did when I was in a place the ward did not go (the Abyss, Epoch III,
the Sea Elven City, Fire Mountain).  Hopefully I did not lose many of those
memories.  I suspect that do to the holographic nature of the brain if you
wipe out ~50% of the brain you lose ~15% of your memories and the remaining
85% just degrade in clarity.

I am suspecting that phase II healing will take about two months and that I
would want to take it easy during that time.

I have run all of this by Alex and he did not balk but is thinking about it
(no commitment yet).

Anybody got any better ideas?  Things to add? Comments?

I am opposed to the idea of doing a healing ritual that just says something
generic like ""you get better"" or ""you restore to pattern"" when the damage is
brain related.  Does that seem unjustified?  I just feel that a natural
healing process (isn't it scary that I consider the thing I just described
as a natural healing process) is safer.

