"RE: Rebuilding Sigmund","This was exectly my concern with getting a little to comic book (my term for
black and white morality and heroes that fight the bad guys 20 hours
straight without resting, going to the bathroom or complaining about being
hungry).  Sigmund is prone to this becuase the major metaphor used for most
of his construction (as well as the Net and the Linking Ward) has been
ultra-high-tech.

At the same time, did I just hear you say that our fantasy campaign is
getting a little unrealistic?  I think perhaps the primary issue is story
balance and then given that it may be appropriate to use reality
manipulations as a screwdriver when it comes to Fortu and the net.

As far as story balance I think that getting wacked by a called short in
close combat with a doppleganger who is using a kata that you have spent
years perfecting should probably set you back a few notches.  Based on the
fact that Fortu are very non-human this could show up in a number of ways
but it ought to show up somehow.  That is why I am still thinking it will
take a couple of days to restore Sigmunds ""physical basis"" and a couple of
months to restore his ""mental integrity"".  Whatever that means.

Given that level of balance I would prefer to make the form of sigmunds
physical healing and ""mental integrity loss"" as strange as possible to
emphasize his non-human nature.  I am continuously looking for good non-tech
metaphors however and perhaps I should work on some now becuase I do not
want Sigmund to get too techy or we lose the flavor of the campaign.

