"Shifters Run description","Allow me to elaborate on your condition and the situation (everyone 
please fill in items I miss):
In the last run Odin had just absorbed the soul of one Death Lord and 
redirected the Lich's link to Corellan.  This decreased the Dark 
covering Marden within a 1000' diameter around the temple of Heimdal. 
Some priests of Usul had launched some spells that further lit up the 
area.

We started the run by finishing the combat that Odin was in the 
middle of at the end of our last session.    Odin charged the Death 
Lord on Sleipnir and managed to survive long enough to hit him a 
couple times.  This weakened the Death Lord enough that its soul 
could be absorbed by the Orb.

Arioch re-appeared although he seemed to be exhausted and kept fading 
out.  Odin was next going to help Miriel (in the form of a platinum 
dragon) in her fight with a Huge Black dragon.  He dropped the Rod of 
Law to Arioch and headed toward Miriel.  Since Miriel was making 
every effort to stay alive but NOT kill the dragon, Odin looked into 
the future to find out what would happen if the dragon died. 
Apparently it was a High Priest of Arken and its death would have 
allowed Arken to join the battle.

Odin headed back to the temple to consult Arioch regarding the 
advisability of that course of action.

On the way he detected 6 Nazgul flying towards the temple and casting 
a ritual.  He updated Arioch (who began casting a spell) and took a 
position a few hundred feet above the temple (Sleipnir stepped in 
place).  He began a big spell.

Meanwhile, Lenore guarded the back of the church and D'Jon sealed it 
from the outside. Falstaff was still fighting earth elementals 
underground.  Inside the temple, Kielsorana was trying to keep the 
Doppleganger from killing E-Man (and then Kielsorana).  Peter, 
Maynard Crosshill (the Lord Chancellor of Heimdal, and Werner Simpson 
(the High Chancellor of Heimdal) did a lot to help.  There were also 
3 priests, 8 Shield, and Amud.  Kielsorana and E-man got kicked 
around a lot, but they managed to stay alive.  E-Man was out of 
commission pretty soon.  After he traded places with Kielsorana as 
the object of the Dopplegangers affection, he used his boon to Arioch 
to give Arioch all but a point of his Power.  Needless to say, E-Man 
was weak as a kitten after that.

Mordanith and Khalid were setting up to fight Khazad Gah (in efreet 
form) and another Efreet.  Khalid created a whirlwind around himself 
and Mordanith and they rose into the air.  Khalid used the Key to 
remove the fire from Khazad Gah and transfer it to the Efreet.  The 
Efreet died, but Khazad Gah was only injured.

The Nazgul's ritual was ripping up the temple of Heimdal and seemed 
likely to bring Arken.  Odin cast a 1000 point Bolt of Damnation 
using the Ravens and the Eye of Odin to target and tune the spell to 
hit all six.  He setup preset actions to immediately shape the power 
released and then Thaumaturgicly Peg it together.  The Bolt succeeded 
in making it so that Three Nazgul had never been.  The resulting 
energy was shaped to Life and then joined with one of the remaining 
Nazgul.  It ""died"".  Four Vorpal blades were destroyed.  The other 
two Nazgul were recalled before Odin could get them

Odin then headed for Khazad Gah who had just gotten thrashed by 
Khalid and Mordanith.  He charged on Sleipnir and through Lightning 
Bolts.  Khazad Gah Dreamwalked away and Odin followed.  Odin managed 
to get one Bolt of three to hit but only blew away his shields. 
Khazad Gah Dreamwalked three times and Odin followed until Khazad Gah 
used a risky Tactic: He Dreamwalked to Fire Mountain.  Then he left 
just as fast as he could.  Odin noticed Kay, Thor and many others 
fighting a retreating battle and joined them.  Mordanith had received 
word that Odin was going to be in trouble and had sent a Light 
grenade to Fire Mountain.  It exploded destroying the Net in that 
area (to what extent I don't know).

As soon as Kielsorana threw the Lich bit to Werner, Kielsorana and 
the Doppleganger were transferred to the Bridge.  Hercules grabbed 
both by the scruff of the neck while Ariel proceeded to determine 
which was which.  Once they determined which one had the worst 
personality, it was released and the other was dragged before the 
throne of power and destroyed.  Hercules was really beat up by the 
Doppleganger but it wouldn't take his form because one of Hercules 
properties is that he cannot be changed.  The Doppleganger obviously 
new this and didn't want to get caught in one form forever.

When notification was given that the Lich bit was in safe keeping, 
Odin and Kay guarded the retreat of the others.  Then the Black 
Dragon that Miriel had been fighting showed up.  Did you know that 
Odin and his High Priest have killed or damaged several Black 
Dragons?  More than any other color.  Apparently this daughter of 
Kisereth has a bone to pick and she wanted that bone to come from 
somewhere in the middle of Odin's chest.  Kay guarded Odin's retreat 
back to Marden.

When Odin got back to Marden and joined the others, the group 
received a message from the Fates, delivered by the Messenger, that 
indicated that for ""eliminating one of the 20, you may have the 
answer to one question"".

I have arranged for you to be put in stasis so that your condition 
doesn't degrade.  You were brought to the Ice Fortress with the rest 
of us when we went to discuss what question we should ask the Fates. 
When we finish the discussion I'll take care of your repairs.

Had you (or any previous incarnation of yourself) set up any preset 
actions or reality triggers in the event that you were rendered 
incapacitated?  (Now would be a good time to let us know)

Chris

