"Re: Gaming (D&D) strategy problem - HELP","Well, as I see it, the biggest problem is the need for Secrecy.  I 
don't know any way of killing a troll quietly (Every time Kheldar has 
killed a Troll it's made a lot of magical noise).

I think that you are making an unnecessary assumption though.  If you 
want to use the Halls of the Dead, why do you have to use a specific 
""hard"" entrance? (and why pick one guarded by a Troll?)

If you were, for example. trying to move several thousand dwarves 
from the Dwarven Mountains, then a minor, but significant, percentage 
of those Dwarves would be Odin worshippers.  Ask a paladin of Odin 
for assistance;  If your cause supports the cause of ORDER, then I'm 
sure that one or more portals could be opened for you.  (other Death 
aspected gods can open portals to the Halls of the Dead, too.)

Taking several thousand (living) dwarves through the Halls would be a 
bit presumptuous, though, unless you have reason to believe that 
you'll get an OK from the Entities in charge.  As an FYI, that isn't 
Odin.

Reality manipulation is difficult around dwarves, but another 
possibility for you would be to create a ""tunnel"" through a more 
""ordered"" plane.

And you could just have them walk ...

Chris

