Let's think of methods to eliminate these.
Vorpal blades work great on solids, but are not too effective on liquid/gas.
(OOH you sliced it!  It flows back into place.)

Strength is only a factor if you can apply it against something.  Ie a
creature with infinite strenght that is floating doesn't punch as hard, the
forward momentum of the fist is balanced with a backwards movement of the
rest of the body.  That's why officials don't break up hocky fights untill
they fall down.  When two guys are standing on skates punching each other,
the damage is minimized.  Just the velocity and mass of the arm, instead of
that plus the hip rotation and legs and other body parts that are fixed to
the ground with a boxer.

