"RE: Sigmund Repair","That IS what we did for the Kilsorana ritual.  We developed ""Restore 
to Pattern"" specifically for that situation.  We didn't actually 
""summon"" Kilsorana's essence.  She went into the Void and was NOT. 
What we did was to get a near perfect blueprint of her pattern (her 
True Name) and recreated her (Damned good job, too).

This is different from the Kilsorana event in two major ways.  On the 
downside, we do not have Sigmund's True Name.  On the upside, we 
*have* Sigmund.

When we use undamaged Sigmund as a reference for repairing damaged 
Sigmund, we are not recreating Sigmund from scratch.  Therefore there 
is nothing missing, at least not as a result of our spell.  Even if 
we aren't repairing him to the exact way that he was, we aren't 
adding anything that he wasn't.  This should at least get him 
operational enough to complete his own repair.

Based on the feedback that we've had from NPC's, I think of RtP with 
this analogy.  RtP is flawed in that its maximum resolution to 
""restore"" is subject to the resolution that is passed to it by the 
""scanner"".  So if we start with a 1200dpi sentient being and we get a 
600dpi pattern, then we end up with a 600dpi being.  If there is a 
better way to ""heal"" then RtP should not be used.  If, however, we 
have a 1200dpi being with a hole in it, then RtP can be used to ""fill 
in the blanks"".  This should be sufficient for the subject to be 
functional once again, with the gap being filled with a ""Band-Aid"" 
until complete healing can occur.

By the way, I have done a lot of research on Haalite.  It may be that 
I have derived enough knowledge from this research to use it as the 
input source for the pattern.  As I'm sure that Sigmund would tell 
you, if he were able to communicate with us, his Rod is Haalite and 
it contains his pattern.  Read correctly, it should be the ideal 
source for his ""undamaged"" pattern.  I will seek guidance from the 
SPIRIT OF THE UNIVERSE (Alex?) to determine if I have sufficient 
knowledge to use it in this fashion.

If not, there are limited options available to us.
1) Fortu DI,
2) I can attempt to bring the Machine sufficiently on-line to restore 
Sigmund as I would restore myself.
3) I can get out my old blueprints and restore him to what he was 
when I built him, which is almost certainly not what he was just 
before the Doppleganger got him.

I welcome any other suggestions, but the final say regarding 
procedure will be given to the Fortu, including Drellan and, if the 
other Fortus agree that it is safe, Big Brother.

Kheldar

