"RE: Sigmund Repair","Most of this stuff is not, IMO, needed to repair Sigmund.

For one thing, he's not dead, or even Voided.  He does, admittedly,
have a whopping great hole (tm) in him, but I am not aware of anything
that would have damaged his base pattern other than the inductive
effect of massively damaging his physical form.

Patterns heal.  All of them.  All we need to do is provide an
appropriate structure for that, take steps so that he doesn't die in
the meantime, and wait.

As a Patterner, I would advise against grafting on parts of old
patterns to plug the wound.  Aside from the difficulty of matching the
edges correctly (and you thought wallpaper was tricky!), patterns
change over time, slowly on some levels and rapidly on others.  The
end result of a pattern-patch is likely to be the equivalent of a
badly-set bone.  While such might well be preferable to death, we are
not performing field surgery here; we have a stable patient and our
choice of techniques and facilities.  (Besides, I don't want to see a
Fortu jihad after we cripple their god.  Not that I would see it for
long, mind you.)

The simplest and safest approach seems to me to be to devise a plug to
insert into his wound that would maintain his basic integrity and
encourage the regrowth of his own natural (at least according to the
current definition) pattern.  The plug could then be subsumed by his
pattern as it heals, and provide the elements it needs to continue
growth.

Maximum safe healing would be to leave him in 'hard' mode for this,
but I'm guessing that would take between 50 and 500 years.  Current
estimates indicate that his pecu-- er, particular abilities may be
needed to save the world some time before that.


After we have his hole plugged, we might want to toss him in a tank of
the appropriate elements, as patternless as possible, and let him
operate as a seed crystal, imposing the pattern he needs on the raw
(or even tuned) elements.  Kheldar's knowledge is probably essential
here, since most of the physical/elemental structure of a Fortu is
probably the same as when he built them.  (Checks new history text.. )
I mean, when he developed the species.


Getting DI from the god of the Fortu might not hurt, either.  He, if
anyone, should know the appropriate patterns.  Heck, he might even
tell us Sigmund's True Name.  (Ya.)


                                           -Myth, Fortu
Deconstructionist.

