Okay.  Myth's Guide to Coping With Realities

1. If you can't tell, then it doesn't matter.

A difference that makes no different is not difference.  I, personally, have
no data that the sun is not a huge fire elemental.  If it were, my current
life would be exactly the same.  (Ignoring, for the moment, possible magical
spin-offs of such a thing.)

2. If it matters, learn how to tell.

If I were a scientist preparing a solar probe, I might well be interested in
determining the nature of the Sun, so that I might design for that
environment.  I would examine rival theories, construct tests, and do other
deterministic stuff.

