Also, Kalarina has been helping a lot with the water zone and Mordenaith had
agreed to help out with some of the wards but if anyone else would like to
pitch in you are always welcome.  I still need to hold a grand openning
party some time soon.

A few tricky design issues I have not yet resolved:

1.  I would like a good 'bouncer' ward to help prevent fights.  One of the
visions of the club is to serve an extremely diverse set of high level
adventurers including people who might be enemies of each other.  I was
originally considering a non-violence-pact ward that you had to agree to
when you entered the club but then I realized that Arak would not be able to
use the club.  I am now thinking of designing a bouncability ward.
Essentially this would require you agree that while you are in the club,
club personal can force you to leave at any time and for any reason
(presumably only for breaking the rules but interpretation is up to us) and
the ward will make it very easy for us to eject the offender and hard for
them to resist ejection.  That way Arak does not need to promise to be
non-violent.  Any better ideas?

2. I am not sure how to structure membership.  At the moment I am thinking
along the lines of must be sponsored by an existing member and club staff
has the right to deny or revoke membership at any time (membership must be
ratified by club staff before it is considered effective).  I would like to
set up the club as a place where high-level NPCs would naturally come when
they want to socialize or meet other high-level NPCs.  What are good ways to
encourage this?  So far I am working on diverse & personalized environments,
good food and drink and entertainment.  I need a good PR strategy though.

3. I think it is important to a club like this to be strongly DIV warded.
Also, it seems that to be a big building in Marden it is a good idea to be
kind of durable.  Beyond this what other kinds of wards do you think I need?
I am thinking of a teleport trap ward just to force people to use the front
doors (and to cut down on assasins).

Anyway, feel free to send me suggestions.

