"A summary of the last run","(I know that some of you dont care about spelling, but I lost my personal
dictionary switching jobs.  If I misspell your characters name, please
correct me and Ill add it to my current dictionary.)  Please feel free to
add your own memories and viewpoints and send them to me.

What happened the last time we got together:

We finally decided to take care of a nagging thorn that had been in our side
for a few years.  Altzar, the Demon lord of Possession, had possessed
Morphus once and given us some serious trouble.  More by luck than skill, we
bypassed his threat by convincing him to pass his will into a few coins that
were then going to be given to Mordanith.  Mordanith did not oblige,
however.  Ever since then, he has been had been trying to get us.  He had
set up some teleport traps that would bring us to him if we teleported
through the area centered on the gate where we last interacted with him.

We did some research and learned that Altzar lives in the 4th Plane of the
Abyss; he is a bifurcated demon; He has taken his essence and locked it
somewhere on the 4th Plane.  Demons of his type are sensitive to Lead.  With
the help of the Master Summoner of Marden (Aelvien), we hoped to lock him on
this plane while we sought his essence and destroyed it.

Kilsorana casts a Mind Shield on Kheldar and links it to me as if I cast it
(10 end/hour) 60 point base.

Kheldar to DJon: {Go to the Monastery; take Sigmunds rod; enlist any
monastery mages that you think necessary.
Watch me through the ballet mirror (elevated view). When I signal you to
Bring me through have an Enchanter use my halite to determine if I am
possessed.  If not, zoom in on me, put your hand through the mirror and draw
me back.  If we have to go through the gate, keep watch on those who remain
to guard Altzar.  Pull my carpet bag through if it looks like it is at
risk.}

The party consisted of Kheldar, Mordanith, Erithmaen, Kilsorana, Sigmund,
Khalid, Arak, and Kor-Keth the Fortu.  The Master Summoner brought along two
sentinels and four (big) lizard-men (with tulwars and studded leather
armor).

We go to Sigmunds club.  I planar travel to the other side of the wall that
secures Sigmunds hard gate to the Paths of the Dead.  We travel and
encounter a 20 wide hole that seems to be Lich flavored.  We pass a 2x3
bound box.  We pass a priest of Usul.  He asks if weve seen a box (we
tell him).  Our destination is the ruined city of Koreth, 100 yards outside
of the library.  When we arrive we see signs of activity at the
archeological dig and a campfire some distance away.  We walk the rest of
the way.  We left most of our loud magic items behind so that we would
have a better chance at surprising him.

{I brought Orb of Souls, Kheldar as dagger; Discipline Sword (100 pt matter
blasts); Staff of Order.  Left most of my items behind or in my carpetbag:
Staff, Soul Collector, KIF focus, Halite Dodecahedron, ring, statue of
Sleipnir}

We set up for our casting.  A containment ward around the gate.  An
un-activated defensive ward within the containment ward.  Summoning circle
within the defensive ward.  Bands of Samara within the Summoning circle.  A
Defensive Ward around the casters.

Kor-Keth sites a Servant of No-Rennan walking towards us.  Arak kills him
through his eye with a crossbow bolt.  I detect that his holy symbol, a
domino(divination) in his pouch, and a pouch full of gold dust (evocation
and fire) are magical.  I isolate these three items with an anti-div circle.
Another human comes through the gate and Arak kills him.

Bands of Samara: (Warder): using Ruby dust

Babboons are attacking, lizard things are trying to get through the gate,
and Altzar has possessed Kilsorana.

End of 12-9-2000 run
Run of 4-22-2001 begins

The Master Summoner succeeds with binding Altzar (Kilsorana)

It is decided that Khalid, Arak, Kor-Keth, Kheldar, & E-Man will retrieve
the essence.  Kheldar signals DJon and DJon pulls us through to a room.
It appears that we have just walked through a ballet mirror (long ceiling
high mirror with a bar running horizontally across the center.)   The mirror
shows where the group was last standing.  I say Show us the essence of
Altzar that is on the 4th Plane of the Abyss.  I am using the Staff of
Order to reinforce the mirrors integrity and that of the portal.  I roll to
determine if the focus is diverted by a phoenix.  Succeeding, we see an
escarpment leading to a well and guarded by two statues.

Kor-Keth goes through stealthed for reconnaissance.  We can see him with an
effort.  When he turns around he unfolds and sets a shield in front of him,
then a sword.  Arak is immediately tense.  We ask and he says that Kor-Keth
must see something above the gate that he believes will attach as soon as he
unstealths and warns us.  He unstealths, and uses battle code to tell us
there are two dragons above the mirror gate.  Dragon fire immediately fills
our view.  When it stops, the sword is a puddle, the shield is glowing red
and Kor-Keth makes it back just in time to shut down.  We immediately
realize that we need more fire power and re-focus the mirror on the rest of
the party.  We give Kor-keth to Sigmund and he is taken to Sigmunds club
for repair.

The Master Summoner says that Amburdus the Mad (Dorian Mage) says that the
Guardians at the Well are bound Slaad.  Dont break them up.

I send Mordanith to the Grove site to do the prep work for his Plane Bore
spell.  Labelas says that he has to do the prep work on the Abyss (Darn!).
I recommend that he do it at the Citadel of the Seven Towers.  He does.  I
focus on Nygolds tower, peg a frog-thing, touch Mordanith with the location
wand and close the mirror.  I bring back Arak and he a few minutes later.

I try to open the mirror on the Abyss again but the Phoenix intercepts.  I
take ten points of damage after a will battle and then close the mirror.  I
get the points back with a potion from Mordanith.

I suggest a diversion.  Mordanith is going to teleport a Bolt of Damnation
trigger covered with our aura, counting on Altzars traps to teleport it to
the Abyss.  Hopefully it will help to divert the Phoenix.  Extremely
hopefully it will trigger the teleport trap.

It does divert the phoenix but we dont know what to do.  We make plans to
Bolt the vessel, and then suck the soul.  DJon goes through to do initial
recon and indicates that the dragons are gone.  The statues immediately
begin to follow him.  He leads them away.  I shift the perspective of our
view and step through the mirror.  Holding the Staff of Order behind me I
launch the Bolt of Damnation that I have prepared and several things happen.
The whole escarpment is a trapped illusion; it dissolves (except for a small
circle around the Staff of Order.)  There are multiple levels of wards in
the well and a reality wall.  The container is a Slaad but the Bolt destroys
it and the wards around it.  I immediately make a will power save and then
attempt to absorb the soul.  Extreme Deific attention is now focused on this
location.

An ancient, large dragon with two heads (1st generation daughter of Kisereth
or manifestation of Kisereth) appears above DJon and is getting ready to
breath fire.  DJon is running for the shield.  The Slaads are headed for
me.  A 40th circle mage (where did he come from?) has just opened a rift to
summon No-Rennon.  A phoenix is approaching.

Kheldar takes Altzars soul and steps backward through the mirror.  The
focus shifts with the essence, effectively isolating the others.  I attempt
to focus on the others but (sorry, forgot exactly what happened here).  I
decide that the rest of the party wont make it back without help.  Odin
rides through on Sleipnir.  He has the spool in addition to the Staff of
Law and Soultaker.

This has drawbacks.  Practically the entire Abyss is focused on the biggest
source of Order that has ever been in the Abyss.  No-Rennan sends tendrils
towards Odin immediately.  Odin uses the spool to draw the others through
the mirror with him (dont ask.).  We then focus on the steps of the temple
of Corellan in Marden.  Odin asks for permission to enter.  This is denied
but Kheldar is given leave to enter.  Odin enters, shifts and follows
Mordanith.  They walk the path to Fairy.

All of us are asked to leave behind holy symbols and related Deific items.
I leave the staff (and sword) behind.  We go to meet Labelas.  We give
Altzar to him.  He asks if we wish a boon.  Britt suggests that we ask for
Kilsorana to be restored.  She is.  Lots of elves want to talk with
Mordanith.  I speak with one about Kheldar, Odin and the spool.  We go back
to Marden.  (OK, Im tired of typing.  There was a little more here).

100 eeps for this run
50 eeps each for the last three runs if we are fairly certain that we didnt
get them already.
